The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Viv quits as chairman of selectors
Bridgetown: Former captain and batting great Vivian Richards has resigned as the chairman of selectors after two years on the job, the West Indies Cricket Board (WICB) said on Sunday. The Antiguan gave up his post after signing a contract with the BBC to work as a radio commentator for this summers internationals, the WICB announced after its directors met in Georgetown. Richards was unavailable for comment. Clyde Butts, the former Guyana and West Indies off-spinner, will replace the 52-year-old Richards on the three member senior panel. Butts remains as chairman of the junior selection committee. Former West Indies opening batsmen Joey Carew and Gordon Greenidge keep their positions on the senior panel. Carew, the 66-year-old Trinidadian, will take over from Richards as chairman.  (AGENCIES)  Copyright 
